%header
  .splash-container
    %strong.splash{ itemprop: "name" } Roman Rott

%main
  %section.links-block.column.justify-center.open-block
    = partial 'partials/links'
    - if open_for_remote
      %h6.center.open-for-remote Open for remote job opportunities. Contact me if you're interested.
    - if open_for_remote == false
      %h6.center.open-for-remote [ I am not currently accepting new job opportunities ]
  %section.content.about-me
    %h1.center
      Hello, my name is
      %span Roman Rott!
    .text-block
      %p
        As an
        %strong Application Security Engineer,
        I bring a wealth of experience as a Full-Stack Ruby/JavaScript developer and Technical Support Representative.
        I have accumulated 17 years of IT expertise throughout my career, with a dedicated focus on web development for more than 10 years.
      %p
        I am deeply interested in penetration testing, red-teaming, and digital forensics, so I have spent the past 3 years expanding my knowledge to transition from Web Development to Cyber Security.
      %p
        As a
        %strong Security Analyst
        and
        %strong Penetration Tester
        for
        %a.print{ href: "https://bsg.tech/", target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' }<
          %strong Berezha Security Group,
        my primary responsibilities involve conducting vulnerability assessments and penetration testing. In addition, I occasionally take part in bug-bounty programs.
  .logo-place
    .logo.responsive
      = partial('images/rrott-ruby-logo.svg').to_s

  %section.content.infosec.dark
    %h2.center Cybersecurity Enthusiast
    .flex
      .center.vw30
      .text-block.infosec-text.vw70
        %p
          I enjoy testing websites for security vulnerabilities (both white-box and black-box) independently, as a part of a team, or on the platforms like BugCrowd.
          During the last 3-4 years, I participated in dozens of
          %strong Web and Mobile Application Security Assessments,
          held
          %strong macOS and Windows Digital Forensics,
          provided
          %strong AWS, EKS,
          and
          %strong Kubernetes Security Audits.
        %p
          I was a member of the latest
          %a.print{ href: "https://nonamecon.org/", target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' }<
            %strong NoNameCon's
          core team - the Ukrainian community-built practical cybersecurity conference.
        %p
          I also used to design, deploy and support vulnerable web and mobile applications for CTF hacking games organized or supported by the
          %a.print{ href: "https://bsg.tech/", target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' }<
            %strong Berezha Security Group
          for:
        %ul
          %li.link
            %a{ href: "https://twitter.com/berezhasecurity/status/1182275892262907905/photo/1", target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' }<
              %strong BruCON 0x0B
            (2019)
            &mdash; (assisted with creating UI for a vulnerable websites)
          %li.link
            %a{ href: "https://nonamecon.org", target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' }<
              %strong NoNameCon
            (2018) &mdash; Practical Cybersecurity Conference (created admin interface, was one of the Game Masters)
          %li.link
            %a{ href: "https://uisgcon.org/en/about-uisgcon", target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' }<
              %strong UISGCon
            \#10, #11, #12 (2014-2016) &mdash; Ukrainian InfoSec conference held by Non Government Organization «Ukrainian Information Security Group»
          %li.link
            The Cybersecurity Olympiad
            %strong «HackIT-2015»
          %li.link
            International forum
            %strong «Cybersecurity: Ukraine and the world»

