            %a{ href: "http://www.vr-online.ru/blog/24hack-khakaton-v-zaporozhe-8785", target: '_blank',rel: 'noopener noreferrer' }<
              «24Hack»
        .recent-blogposts
          %h3.oss-text.padding2 Recent posts from my blog:
          %ul
            - blog.articles[0...3].each do |article|
              %li.link
                %a{ href: "#{article.url}", title: "#{article.title}" }
                  %time{ datetime: article.date}="#{article.date.strftime('%b %e %Y')}"
                  &mdash; #{article.title}
            %li.link
              %a{ href: "/blog/", title: "link to my blog" }
                Read more...

  %section.dark.content.dev-skills
    %h2.center Former Web Developer
    .stickers
      .logo.responsive.wrap.justify-center
        - ['react', 'redux', 'ruby', 'rails', 'svelte', 'html5', 'css', 'js'].each do |sticker|
          .sticker{ class: sticker }

      .text-block.vw70
        Throughout my 9-year tenure at IxWebhosting.com, a large Shared and Cloud Hosting company, I worked in various departments in different positions. During this time, I spent 5 years working in the 
        %strong Tech Support department
        and 4 years as a Ruby/Rails Developer in the IT department.
        %p
        There I gained a wealth of experience dealing with code written by other developers, focusing on
        %strong troubleshooting, debugging, and fixing code.
        Additionally, I gained extensive experience in detecting and resolving security flaws and bugs.
        %p
        Afterward, I spent another 5 years working as a Full-Stack Ruby Developer for various US and Europ companies. Meanwhile, I've designed and developed intentionally vulnerable applications for CTF hacking games, which provide a platform for security enthusiasts to practice and enhance their skills.
        %p
        My
        %a{ href: "/portfolio/" }<
          portfolio as a Full-Stack Web Developer
        provides a brief summary of project samples that I completed before transitioning into the Cybersecurity field.

